  "chunk_index": 19,
  "summary": "Inspector Spence visits David Hunter and Rosaline Claude at their residence to investigate the murder of the man known as Enoch Yates, who was found dead at the Stagg Inn with his head bashed in. Spence reveals that Yates claimed to be a friend of the late Robert André and suggested that André might still be alive. David dismisses these claims as a hoax, asserting that Robert was his sister's first husband who died of blackwater fever in Africa.\n\nWhen Spence questions David regarding his whereabouts between 7:00 PM and 11:00 PM the previous night, David refuses to answer, stating he dislikes being coerced. Spence warns him that he will be summoned for formal questioning. To advance the case, Spence requests that Rosaline identify the body, noting that a witness heard the deceased mention the name Robert. David supports Rosaline's decision to comply, and Spence arranges for a Daimler rental car to transport them to the morgue.\n\nDuring the drive, Rosaline appears visibly terrified and pale. She whispers to the sergeant that she is fearful due to a past trauma in London, where she was the sole survivor of an air raid that killed everyone in her house. David encourages her to be brave, telling her that the deceased will look peaceful.",
